@675  = ~My time is quick, so be brief, commoner.~ [NOBMA03]
@676  = ~May I help you?~
@677  = ~What do you do here?~
@678  = ~I don't need anything right now.~
@679  = ~Malficus sent me.~
@680  = ~So, do I get a reward for doing your dirty work?~
@681  = ~I'm surprised to see you. I thought you would be decorating some gallows, by now.~
@682  = ~Then I have no time for you. Good day.~
@683  = ~I keep Athkatla's harbor, the largest in Amn and second only to Waterdeep, running at peak efficiency. As you may well imagine, I am a very busy man.~
@684  = ~What are you doing here, then? Shouldn't you be at the Docks?~
@685  = ~What are your duties, exactly?~
@686  = ~Sounds boring.~
@687  = ~You don't look very busy.~
@688  = ~I'm looking for information about someone taken by the Cowled Wizards.~
@689  = ~Farewell.~
@690  = ~I have no time for such folly. Good day.~
@691  = ~A great many things. Good day.~
@692  = ~I suggest you ask a Cowled Wizard. Good day.~
@693  = ~Hmf.~
@694  = ~You must be joking... except that I see you are not. Very well, I shall be brief. Malficus secured your silence?~
@695  = ~My silence is like my loyalty: reserved for the highest bidder.~
@696  = ~I am sworn to secrecy.~
@697  = ~More or less.~
@698  = ~Just tell me what you want me to do.~
@699  = ~Unacceptable. Begone before I have you arrested for conspiracy.~
@700  = ~Calm down. I won't talk.~
@701  = ~That would be ironic. You're the one that wants someone assassinated.~
@702  = ~You'd be dead before the words left your lips.~
@703  = ~I want you to remove Harbormaster Nador.~
@704  = ~Why?~
@705  = ~How banal.~
@706  = ~Could this assignment be any more trivial?~
@707  = ~I'll do it.~
@708  = ~Where can I find him?~
@709  = ~On second thought, I won't do it.~
@710  = ~Excellent.~
@711  = ~You are mistaken. I merely asked if Malficus has secured your silence. I did not ask toward what end. Nevertheless, you strike me as an unreliable character. I will have no further business with you. Good day.~
@712  = ~Perhaps, but how far would you get before you, too, were slain? No, <PRO_SIRMAAM>, you cannot be that foolish. Go now.~
@713  = ~You must be new to Athkatla. No one familiar with Athkatlan politics would utter anything so inane. Ambition, my good <PRO_MANWOMAN>, is the moving force in the City of Coin.~
@714  = ~Are you interested?~
@715  = ~I'm uncomfortable with the thought of doing this in cold blood.~
@716  = ~Your opinion is noted and filed. Are you in?~
@717  = ~A task like this requires discretion, of course. An assault in his office would likely prove ineffective and probably fatal to the perpetrators.~
@718  = ~Subtlety will carry the day, and poison is the most subtle of the assassin's tools. Harbormaster Nador will dine at the Vulova estate this evening. As the Harbormaster requires a particular diet, dishes will be prepared specially for him and eaten only by him.~
@719  = ~The cook in the Vulova kitchen expects the delivery of some rare ingredients for Harbormaster Nador's repast. Once you have secured them, the butler at the estate can direct you to the kitchen.~
@720  = ~Seems like a lot of people already know about this.~
@721  = ~Won't it be obvious that Nador is poisoned, if he's eating food no one else is eating?~
@722  = ~Where do I get the "special ingredients," again?~
@723  = ~No. I won't do it.~
@724  = ~Unfortunate, but you are within your rights by refusing.~
@725  = ~I must remind you of your promised silence. Speak of this to anyone, and our friend at the Mithrest Inn will refuse to have further dealings with you.~
@726  = ~Understood.~
@727  = ~We'll see.~
@728  = ~Few enough.~
@729  = ~The condition that compells the good Harbormaster to keep to a prescribed diet might also explain his sudden demise. The specific "ingredient" has been chosen because it would arouse no undue suspicion.~
@730  = ~There is a man on the second floor of the Five Flagons Inn, in the large parlor beyond the guest rooms. He can supply what you need.~
@731  = ~Now, if you will excuse me, I must return to my office to attend some rather tedious paperwork. Good day.~
@732  = ~Will you do it? Yes or no.~
@733  = ~Unfortunate, but understandable. As it happens, I can put you in touch with a man who can spare you the necessity of becoming personally involved.~
@734  = ~Tell me more.~
@735  = ~No, I can't do it at all.~
@736  = ~The man's name is Wael. He frequents Delosar's Inn, as I recall. You can usually find him on the first floor.~
@737  = ~I will seek him out.~
@738  = ~I'm not sure... no, I can't do this.~
@739  = ~You do that.~
@740  = ~I believe our friend Malficus has negotiated your reward. It came in the form of a quite substantial reduction in the cost of a voyage, if I understand correctly.~
@741  = ~Now, I am a very busy man. Good day.~
@742  = ~Oh, there was an inquiry, never fear, but there was never any substantiated evidence against me, no thanks to you.~
@743  = ~Now, if you do not leave at once, I will have you charged with harassment.~
@744  = ~Ahh, I know a discerning eye when I see one.~ [MYSTR01]
@745  = ~Who are you?~
@746  = ~Ballas told me that you have something that I need.~
@747  = ~Would you know where a person could make a few discrete purchases?~
@748  = ~Sorry for bothering you. I'll be on my way.~
@749  = ~I am no one of consequence, though you may call me Vhellon.~
@750  = ~Could you tell me where I might be able to find some interesting merchandise?~
@751  = ~Ballas said you have something for me.~
@752  = ~What is there to see in the Bridge District?~
@753  = ~You don't say! Well, if you have the coin, I have what you need. Fifty gold.~
@754  = ~I'll give you twenty.~
@755  = ~Done.~
@756  = ~I don't have that much coin.~
@757  = ~I might have something you're interested in. Just keep it quiet, see?~
@758  = ~Show me what you've got.~
@759  = ~No thanks.~
@760  = ~No bother.~
@761  = ~Do I look like a tour guide? Go ask one of the merchants in the street.~
@762  = ~Are you a merchant?~
@763  = ~No need to be rude about it.~
@764  = ~And done.~
@765  = ~Not good enough.~
@766  = ~Oh, all right. Here's your money.~
@767  = ~I don't have that kind of gold.~
@768  = ~Come back when you do.~
@769  = ~Speak, if ye will.~ [STHMA02]
@770  = ~I hear you're good at making problems go away.~
@771  = ~I need a favor.~
@772  = ~I thought I could do this, but I can't.~
@773  = ~What do you need?~
@774  = ~Assistant Harbormaster Ballas asked me to poison Harbormaster Nador.~
@775  = ~Nothing. I can't do this. I just can't.~
@776  = ~It happens. Good luck to you.~
@777  = ~Not an easy job. A hundred gold.~
@778  = ~Here. Just don't tell me any more about it.~
@779  = ~I don't have a hundred gold.~
@780  = ~Too bad. Well, I'm not going anywhere.~
@781  = ~Greetings. How do you do?~ [B!NADOR]
@782  = ~Are you aware that your assistant is trying to have you assassinated?~
@783  = ~I'd like to hire a ship.~
@784  = ~I am Harbormaster Nador. I oversee and enforce the regulations of the harbor. I ensure that the pilots operate in accordance with Athkatlan policy, that docking and unloading tarrifs are paid appropriately, and mediate any disputes that may arise.~
@785  = ~You must be a very busy man.~
@786  = ~Ah. Now I know.~
@787  = ~So... can I hire a ship?~
@788  = ~Good day.~
@789  = ~Indeed! You should bring this to Chief Inspector Brega's attention at once!~
@790  = ~Now if you will excuse me, I really must be going. I have an important affair to attend this evening, and it seems that I shall have to engage additional security staff.~
@791  = ~I'd like to help you, but I'm afraid you'll have to find a captain willing to fulfil your request. My office handles matters that relate to the port, not the ships that use it. Good day.~
@792  = ~Indeed. I am so far behind, I'm surprised I haven't met myself coming. It's been a pleasure chatting with you. Do enjoy your stay in the City of Coin.~
@793  = ~Indeed. Do enjoy your stay in Athkatla.~
@794  = ~And the same to you, my good <PRO_SIRMAAM>.~
@795  = ~I understand I have you to thank for my continued existence?~
@796  = ~That's right. Is there a reward?~
@797  = ~It was the right thing to do.~
@798  = ~I had nothing to do with it.~
@799  = ~Are you being more careful, these days?~
@800  = ~I can offer you this small token of gratitude. It isn't much, but my expenses are more than they were, with the extra security, and all.~
@801  = ~I rather thought so, but I'm rather biased, I admit.~
@802  = ~You're too modest, but you have my thanks.~
@803  = ~Yes, I have to be. Sometimes, I feel like a prisoner in my own house, but at least I'm safe... but then, I thought I was safe before, so we'll have to see what happens.~
@804  = ~Lord Vulova's parties are always so enjoyable.~
@805  = ~Say, didn't we meet last year at Lady Jysstev's spring soire?~
@806  = ~I do hope dinner will be served soon. I've developed quite an appetite.~
@807  = ~Isn't it a delightful evening?~
@808  = ~I have a delivery for the kitchen.~
@809  = ~No, I don't think so.~
@810  = ~You are expected. Just take it back to the kitchen, will you? You'll find the cook inside.~
@811  = ~We are expecting a delivery, but I don't see any packages. Perhaps you neglected to collect it?~
@812  = ~No matter, we still have a few moments. Go get it, but make haste. We've already delayed dinner as long as we really can.~
@813  = ~Away with you, then. We are expecting an important delivery, and it seems to be running late.~
@814  = ~You need something, stranger?~ [GENMG04]
@815  = ~I have something for you.~
@816  = ~No, nothing at all.~
@817  = ~Well, hand it over. They've been screaming for their dinner for ages.~
@818  = ~I don't think you do. No go get it, so we can get this whole business over with.~
@819  = ~Then get out of my kitchen.~
@820  = ~My, but I do find myself in charming company! Linger after dinner, if you will, and allow me to show you around my estate.~
@821  = ~Come hither, my sweet-faced little elf, and sit on my knee.~
@822  = ~I don't think I should do that, my lord.~
@823  = ~Don't be afraid, my dear. I'm quite the gentle old man.~
@824  = ~Excuse me.... I have to go.~
@825  = ~Why, if it isn't little Nalia D'Arnise!~
@826  = ~You've grown into quite the fine young woman. Yes... very fine indeed.~
@827  = ~Lord Vulova, you haven't changed a bit. A pity.~
@828  = ~Strange, but I don't remember inviting you. I must consult the guest list.~
@829  = ~If you're making a delivery, kindly take it up with the butler.~
@830  = ~Excuse me, but this is a private conversation.~
@831  = ~If you see that blasted cook about, ask him why dinner is so late.~
@832  = ~Why, you're Anomen Delryn, aren't you? Have I ever introduced you to my daughter?~
@833  = ~Indeed, madam, you have not.~
@834  = ~We should remedy this at once!~
@835  = ~Madam, please! This is hardly the place for introductions, and my duties do not allow much leisure, in any case. Forgive me.~
@836  = ~Lord Vulova really should limit his invitation list. I don't remember when I've been so warm.~
@837  = ~Dress customs are insufferably lax, these days. I remember a time when a person wouldn't be caught dead wearing armor to a dinner party.~
@838  = ~I hear the price of iron is going up again. That bodes ill for the city, I tell you.~
@839  = ~Do I know you? No, I'm certain I have no connections that low.~
@840  = ~I can't believe my bad luck. Just the other day, I had some valuable documents stolen from me. You'd think they'd be safe, after what I paid for that box.~
@841  = ~I have information that you may find interesting. Assistant Harbormaster Ballas is plotting against Harbormaster Nador.~
@842  = ~Is he, now? I suppose ye have proof to back up this accusation?~
@843  = ~Not exactly, no.~
@844  = ~He tried to hire me to assassinate him.~
@845  = ~What kind of proof?~
@846  = ~We can't move on Ballas without concrete evidence, but I'll have a few of the lads look into it. Thank ye for bringing this to my attention.~
@847  = ~What, have ye got proof? I need something solid if I'm going to get this to stick. A contract, or sommat.~
@848  = ~No, we don't have a contract.~
@849  = ~What kind of proof do you want?~
@850  = ~Does anyone actuallly do that? Sign a contract for an assassination?~
@851  = ~Can you at least tell Harbormaster Nador to forgo the banquet at the Vulova estate? That's where it's supposed to happen.~
@852  = ~I should have known better than to leave this in the hands of the bureaucrats.~
@853  = ~Something I can put my hands on. A document, a witness, something more than your word against his.~
@854  = ~Keldorn was there. He can tell you what he saw.~
@855  = ~Anomen heard everything. He can back me up.~
@856  = ~Aerie, can you tell Chief Inspector Brega what you heard?~
@857  = ~Haer'Dalis can verify everything I said.~
@858  = ~Tell the man, will you, Jaheira.~
@859  = ~Yoshimo, if you would...~
@860  = ~Would you do the honors, Edwin?~
@861  = ~Cernd will back me here.~
